body:
@Hubro sorry I didn't see this sooner. I've been using a minimally patched version without problems for more than a year at this point: https://github.com/bard/syncthing/tree/instant-sync (it's not in sync with upstream though).

It works just fine with sub-second delays, file synchronization is near immediate and I haven't seen side effects (e.g. when synchronizing large amount of files). 

The only thing preventing official Syncthing from doing the same is that the configuration delay parameter is implemented as an integer. In the fork, I hacked around thtat by leaving the parameter as integer but making Syncthing interpret it as milliseconds.  I've tried to make a case in this issue for a proper fix, changing the parameter type to a float (see discussion above) but without luck.
